# Linux Fundamentals Part 1

**Room URL**: [TryHackMe-Linux Fundamentals Part 1](https://tryhackme.com/room/linuxfundamentalspart1)

## Summary
This room introduced me to working in a Linux environment â€” a fundamental skill for anyone in cybersecurity. I learned how to move around the filesystem, inspect files, and use the terminal confidently. It laid the groundwork for interacting with real systems during assessments or investigations.

## Tools & Techniques Used
- Shell navigation and commands (`ls`, `cd`, `pwd`)
- Viewing file contents (`cat`, `less`, `head`, `tail`)
- Understanding Linux directory hierarchy

## Key Skills Learnt
- Built confidence using the terminal in a Linux environment.
- Learned how to efficiently locate and understand system files.
- Established a baseline for deeper Linux-based investigations and operations.
